The paper discusses low-rank modeling, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision. The use of nonconvex low-rank regularizers is also mentioned, which is a popular area of research in optimization and signal processing. The experiments conducted involve matrix completion and robust principal component analysis, which are both topics in data science. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves signal processing and optimization, which could fall under cs.SI (Signal Processing) and cs.IT (Information Theory), respectively.
